    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>123700</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Πειθαγόρας">Πειθαγόρας</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἰάσων">Ἰάσονος</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Peithagoras fils d'Iasôn.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Peithagoras son of Iason.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Peithagoras figlio di Iason.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>Iason was a very common name at Cyrene, Peithagoras has also some occurrences. No prosopographical relation can be suggested.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
